crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a backdoor/RAT. It establishes command-and-control (C2) communication with `jdkgradle.com` via the endpoint `/jdk/update/update.php`. The malware can receive commands to execute arbitrary shell commands via `popen` (e.g., `"%s 2>&1 &"`), upload and download files, and execute payloads. C2 communications are encrypted using a custom XOR cipher with the key `"wLqfM]%wTx`~tUTbw>R^"` and then Base64 encoded.
